@Enigmaticjones @NGB2020 Well, I WILL say that before my bariatric surgery, I drank soda CONSTANTLY, especially root beer and birch beer. Birch beer was my favorite drink for decades, esp. when I lived up north. My favorite root beers were Mug, followed by IBC, A&W, Hires, and Barq's.

@Enigmaticjones @NGB2020 My favorite birch beers are Boylan's, Pennsylvania Dutch, and Polar...the last of which is about the only brand you're likely to see in ANY store south of the Mason-Dixon line. I live in NC, and have since 1987, and unfortunately, birch beer is a rarity outside of New England.

@Enigmaticjones @NGB2020 But to me, white birch beer (the clear kind) is the best (I'm not a fan of the red varieties), and is like a sweeter, smoother, tastier version of root beer. If I was going to drink a soda now, it would DEFINITELY be birch beer.
